metadata.name: Sanctuarium
metadata.description:
Neon sign lights bursting cities crumble
Nomads, looking for a place of a world.

Welcomes the different opens his eyes looks around
here it is, The Sanctuary of the World.

Gold screens, data smears, precious, such as oil.

I am black but I am beautiful in my eye there is a star.

Look at me, I'm different, you are too.

I'm black and I'm a woman, I don't want a pedestal for that.

They are the hymn to welcome, a distant light.

I'm here to let you in, I'm a beacon of hope.
